drive this far to pick up a passenger.

125
00:11:08,290 --> 00:11:09,130
So?

126
00:11:09,360 --> 00:11:10,370
Get in my car.

127
00:11:13,190 --> 00:11:14,590
I'll tip a bit extra.

128
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:15,650
Someone will come.

129
00:11:18,810 --> 00:11:20,460
If you listen to me,

130
00:11:21,290 --> 00:11:22,040
there's a chance

131
00:11:23,470 --> 00:11:25,070
I'll tell you

132
00:11:25,100 --> 00:11:26,300
what happened last night.

133
00:11:31,210 --> 00:11:31,940
Where are we going?

134
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,920
You'll see.

135
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:46,300
Isn't this near our high school?

136
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:47,640
Yes.

137
00:11:48,510 --> 00:11:49,650
Why did you bring me here?

138
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,790
Let me find a parking space first.

139
00:11:54,210 --> 00:11:55,530
I've already come with you.

140
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:56,760
Are you going to tell me or not?

141
00:11:58,510 --> 00:11:59,220
About what?

142
00:12:00,490 --> 00:12:01,110
About...

143
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:02,810
About whether we

144
00:12:04,720 --> 00:12:05,930
did it or not yesterday.

145
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:34,310
What do you mean by

146
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:36,500
"did it"?

147
00:12:37,580 --> 00:12:38,290
So annoying.

148
00:12:38,290 --> 00:12:40,000
Zhang Yiqing, tell me already.

149
00:12:40,090 --> 00:12:42,040
I'll get off if you don't tell me.

150
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:45,250
You fell asleep outside,

151
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,370
and I carried you inside.

152
00:12:47,470 --> 00:12:49,310
I couldn't have left you out there and let you scare people, could I?

153
00:12:50,050 --> 00:12:52,470
And you spilled wine on yourself,

154
00:12:53,430 --> 00:12:54,750
so I had to help you change.

155
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:57,430
Or else you'd have to dirty the hotel bed.

156
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:02,800
So all we did was...

157
00:13:02,830 --> 00:13:04,100
Changing my clothes?

158
00:13:07,970 --> 00:13:09,630
Do you expect us to have done something else?

159
00:13:17,560 --> 00:13:18,520
There's a parking space ahead.

160
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:27,550
What era is this?

161
00:13:27,830 --> 00:13:29,170
Why are there still people physically reserving a parking space?

162
00:13:38,180 --> 00:13:39,130
He took my parking space.

163
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:40,270
Of course I should honk at him.

164
00:13:43,130 --> 00:13:43,980
What are you doing?

165
00:13:44,450 --> 00:13:45,220
He took your parking space.

166
00:13:45,220 --> 00:13:46,280
Of course we should honk at him.

167
00:13:46,890 --> 00:13:47,670
Forget it.

168
00:13:47,810 --> 00:13:49,070
I parked too slowly myself.

169
00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:50,950
You're just too steady and slow.

170
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:52,260
You never ran a yellow light,

171
00:13:52,260 --> 00:13:54,260
never sped, and never got a ticket.

172
00:13:54,260 --> 00:13:56,030
You never handed in any assignments late, skipped any classes,

173
00:13:56,030 --> 00:13:57,730
and you were always top three for every exam.

174
00:13:57,730 --> 00:13:58,930
Don't you think your life is too boring,

175
00:13:58,930 --> 00:13:59,670
Zhang Yiqing?

176
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:03,600
Are you upset about

177
00:14:07,190 --> 00:14:08,490
me scolding you in the car last time?

178
00:14:10,220 --> 00:14:11,730
All I care about is whether

179
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:15,690
you like me better the way I am now.

180
00:14:26,160 --> 00:14:27,630
Do you know the difference

181
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:28,660
between a big tree and a small tree?

182
00:14:29,550 --> 00:14:30,300
I don't.

183
00:14:30,830 --> 00:14:32,870
They're both planted in the ground.

184
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:34,050
True.

185
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,120
You're boring.

186
00:14:37,350 --> 00:14:38,070
Wait a moment.

187
00:14:38,090 --> 00:14:39,130
I need to take this.

188
00:14:41,280 --> 00:14:46,850
♫I want to grow closer to you day by day♫

189
00:14:46,850 --> 00:14:52,620
♫I want to write a diary together with you♫

190
00:14:52,620 --> 00:14:55,890
♫We defied gravity♫

191
00:14:55,890 --> 00:14:59,090
♫To come here and exchange rings♫

192
00:14:59,090 --> 00:15:02,100
♫Revealing♫

193
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:07,430
♫The secret which belongs to us♫

194
00:15:09,570 --> 00:15:12,840
♫We defied gravity♫

195
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:15,910
♫To come here and exchange rings♫

196
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:17,480
♫Because of you♫

197
00:15:18,710 --> 00:15:23,850
♫I can be myself again♫

198
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:28,810
Thank you.

199
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:31,860
Thank you.

200
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,150
Ian?

201
00:15:59,410 --> 00:16:00,420
You must have waited long.

202
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,510
I'm back.

203
00:16:13,110 --> 00:16:14,550
Why didn't you tell me in advance

204
00:16:14,570 --> 00:16:15,980
that you were coming back from abroad?

205
00:16:16,390 --> 00:16:17,990
I asked Tang Duzhi to keep it a secret.

206
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,110
I wanted to give you a surprise.

207
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,380
Ian's company has always been working closely

208
00:16:25,380 --> 00:16:26,930
with Hongze Funeral Directors.

209
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,340
Back in high school,

210
00:16:31,420 --> 00:16:33,200
we got assigned to the same group for assignments a lot, didn't we?

211
00:16:33,230 --> 00:16:34,240
We have great chemistry.

212
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:36,260
I told your brother that

213
00:16:36,590 --> 00:16:37,990
if you're willing to take over,

214
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:39,400
I'll definitely have your back.

215
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:41,680
It's just...

216
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:43,930
Do you really want to take over?

217
00:16:47,970 --> 00:16:49,470
When you were watching the performance just now,

218
00:16:49,470 --> 00:16:50,790
you were so focused.

219
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,840
What about your music dream?

220
00:16:54,580 --> 00:16:55,470
I...

221
00:16:58,880 --> 00:16:59,710
I'm not sure yet.

222
00:17:02,920 --> 00:17:03,700
It's okay.

223
00:17:04,390 --> 00:17:05,670
No matter what decision you make,

224
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:07,230
I'll support you all the way.

225
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:12,210
Ian just got his MBA degree from the US.

226
00:17:13,130 --> 00:17:14,800
So he'll share his knowledge and information

227
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,710
on corporate management with you.

228
00:17:16,880 --> 00:17:18,210
So he'll participate in the upcoming training sessions

229
00:17:18,490 --> 00:17:19,599
together with us.

230
00:17:20,300 --> 00:17:21,210
Together?

231
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:22,470
So,

232
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:24,290
you'll be living with us?

233
00:17:25,260 --> 00:17:27,460
Yes, this is the second surprise.

234
00:17:31,060 --> 00:17:32,460
I just made a reservation at a restaurant.

235
00:17:34,170 --> 00:17:35,460
Let's talk over dinner.

236
00:17:35,910 --> 00:17:37,120
Okay, let me see.

237
00:17:40,640 --> 00:17:41,570
I think this restaurant

238
00:17:41,590 --> 00:17:43,170
is a bit too formal.

239
00:17:43,820 --> 00:17:45,910
I suddenly thought of a restaurant I've been dying to eat at.

240
00:17:46,290 --> 00:17:47,420
For nostalgic reasons.

241
00:17:47,950 --> 00:17:49,070
Can we go to that restaurant instead?

242
00:17:50,340 --> 00:17:51,380
I'm sorry.

243
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:53,060
I didn't look into your preferences in advance.

244
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,330
It's up to you.

245
00:17:54,740 --> 00:17:55,520
It's okay.

246
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:01,400
Let's go. I'll take you to eat.

247
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:06,160
Don't you think he's a bit too serious?

248
00:18:06,280 --> 00:18:07,250
He just looks that way.

249
00:18:07,250 --> 00:18:08,330
You'll see later.

250
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:29,250
This brings back memories.

251
00:18:29,860 --> 00:18:30,830
It's really been a long time.

252
00:18:32,530 --> 00:18:34,110
Look, the wall has been renovated.

253
00:18:34,540 --> 00:18:36,040
When you climbed up that wall,

254
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:37,000
I always felt it would collapse.

255
00:18:37,970 --> 00:18:39,410
At that time, I wasn't afraid of anything

256
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:42,430
but being caught by that instructor.

257
00:18:42,990 --> 00:18:44,880
You were afraid of the math teacher too, okay?

258
00:18:45,460 --> 00:18:46,960
Every time you forgot to do your homework,

259
00:18:47,050 --> 00:18:47,920
you asked me to help you.

260
00:18:47,920 --> 00:18:49,100
Not every time, okay?

261
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,530
By the way, you were too slow.

262
00:18:50,550 --> 00:18:52,140
It was because of you that I almost got caught by the instructor.

263
00:18:52,660 --> 00:18:53,660
I was too slow?

264
00:18:53,660 --> 00:18:54,500
Yeah.

265
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:56,400
Let's have a race now if you dare.

266
00:18:57,230 --> 00:18:58,810
Why did you start early?

267
00:19:16,680 --> 00:19:18,030
Is this the restaurant you want to eat at?

268
00:19:18,390 --> 00:19:20,290
Yes, I haven't been here for a long time.

269
00:19:20,490 --> 00:19:21,700
I missed it.

270
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:22,730
Let's eat.

271
00:19:26,130 --> 00:19:27,530
Wang Zhan, listen.

272
00:19:27,560 --> 00:19:29,500
You should mix the braised pork rice like this,

273
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:33,030
so that the braising sauce evenly coats each grain of rice.

274
00:19:33,030 --> 00:19:34,750
Only then can you truly taste how delicious it is.

275
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:35,960
Let me mix it for you.

276
00:19:40,040 --> 00:19:40,860
Here, try it.

277
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:42,090
Thank you.

278
00:19:45,410 --> 00:19:45,950
How is it?

279
00:19:46,670 --> 00:19:47,700
Not bad.

280
00:19:47,810 --> 00:19:48,490
Right?

281
00:19:50,340 --> 00:19:51,540
Try mixing too.

282
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:52,680
It's really delicious.

283
00:19:53,090 --> 00:19:54,090
Just enjoy your meal.

284
